HEADWORD: Gonad
<hw>Gon"ad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Gonads</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr. <?/ that which
generates.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the masses of
generative tissue primitively alike in both sexes, but giving rise to
either an ovary or a testis; a generative gland; a germ gland.</def>
<rj><au>Wiedersheim.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

